00:03:43.276 --> 00:03:45.276
travel through the dimensions in time.

00:03:46.676 --> 00:03:47.617
And for that to happen,

00:03:47.638 --> 00:03:52.639
he was going to have to find someone,

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:54.480
a life form that was

00:03:56.792 --> 00:04:00.832
observant, responsive, thoughtful,

00:04:03.775 --> 00:04:07.415
one that was absolutely willing and

00:04:07.556 --> 00:04:12.337
enthusiastic about engaging with him,

00:04:12.418 --> 00:04:14.138
and then someone he could trust.

00:04:16.059 --> 00:04:18.759
And the first man, his firstborn,

00:04:20.860 --> 00:04:21.480
didn't measure up.

00:04:22.745 --> 00:04:25.165
And what God realized is that he would

00:04:25.305 --> 00:04:30.146
never have measured up to his potential if

00:04:30.187 --> 00:04:33.588
that potential existed at all inside the

00:04:33.627 --> 00:04:38.749
protective confines of Eden, no.

00:04:40.009 --> 00:04:43.769
Man would have to gain experience on his

00:04:43.850 --> 00:04:45.711
own apart from God.

00:04:45.771 --> 00:04:49.430
He would have to observe his environment,

00:04:49.550 --> 00:04:51.372
shape it to his survival.

00:04:53.961 --> 00:04:55.882
engage in the process of life,

00:04:58.744 --> 00:05:00.324
make mistakes, learn from them,

00:05:01.086 --> 00:05:03.067
fall and get back up.

00:05:05.007 --> 00:05:07.728
All showing that in a world full of

00:05:07.809 --> 00:05:09.750
obstacles, challenges,

00:05:10.730 --> 00:05:11.930
that he could pass muster,

00:05:12.571 --> 00:05:16.012
that he could show himself worthy of being

00:05:16.932 --> 00:05:19.954
